      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HEZ HARRYWHO (6) settled in the leading division then found the lead only to be claimed in the straight and finish second last start over 1650m at Bendigo, that run on the back of a good second at Kilmore the run before. Ideally placed and is sure to prove tough to beat. WINGATE GUY (2) settled well back then made a long sustained run at his most recent outing and finished fourth, beaten a neck, in a far better performance at Bendigo over 2150m. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run and rates a big chance in a similar race. LEONARD (9) is better than his first-up seventh over 1750m at Swan Hill two weeks ago. Strips fitter now. OUR CHEEKY DEVIL (4) is the best of the rest after finishing fourth over 1690m at Kilmore last time out.",
